<!-- Slide 12: Personalization thesis + ownership paths -->
<div class="content-slide personalization">
  <p class="overline">The Real Lesson</p>
  <h2><span class="highlight">Own</span> the Harness</h2>
  <p class="lead personalization__lead">
    The model is not the part you control. The harness is: what context enters, which tools run,
    how work is routed, when results are trusted, and what gets kept.
  </p>

  <div class="ownership">
    <div class="ownership__thesis">
      <span class="ownership__kicker">The default is already a choice</span>
      <h3>Your harness decides how the agent works.</h3>
      <p>OmO, RTK, cocoindex-code, and the optimizer loop are not just tools. They are examples of harness decisions.</p>
      <p class="ownership__line">The move is not to adopt every opinion. The move is to make the useful ones yours.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ownership__paths">
      <div class="ownership-path ownership-path--adopt">
        <span class="ownership-path__badge">Start rich</span>
        <h3>Adopt &amp; Reshape</h3>
        <p>Start from a rich harness like OmO. Disable what you do not need, keep the patterns that help, and replace defaults that do not fit.</p>
        <span class="ownership-path__trade">Fast power. Ownership comes from reshaping.</span>
      </div>

      <div class="ownership-path ownership-path--build">
        <span class="ownership-path__badge">Start minimal</span>
        <h3>Build Up</h3>
        <p>Start from vanilla OpenCode or a minimalist harness like Pi, then add skills and one small plugin. Add RTK, semantic search, routing, or eval loops only when pain shows up.</p>
        <span class="ownership-path__trade">Maximum transparency. Power grows from real needs.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="roads__destination">
    <p class="roads__destination-line">Goal: not the fanciest setup. A setup you understand, can debug, and can change.</p>
  </div>
</div>
